        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 8:28AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 828 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Stanley, moving east southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.

Locations in or near the path include...
Eubanks...                        Clayton Lake State Park...
Sardis...                         Snow...
Tuskahoma...                      Clayton...
Stanley...                        Nashoba...
Kiamichi...                       Kosoma...
Albion...                         Dunbar...
Finley...                         Honobia...
Cloudy...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
